===== audit-map/25-accounts-routing/desired-provider-account-plan.md =====
# Desired Provider Account Plan

This plan reflects the current intended account surface for the AirMentor audit environment.

## Arctic Slot Strategy

The installed Arctic build on this machine does not expose the documented `arctic auth login <provider> --name <account>` flag in CLI help and rejected local `--name` attempts.

Therefore, multi-account handling is implemented through isolated Arctic state directories per slot instead of shared global auth.

Each slot gets:

- `~/.local/share/air-mentor-audit/arctic-slots/<slot>/data`
- `~/.config/air-mentor-audit/arctic-slots/<slot>/config`

## Planned Slots

| Slot | Provider | Intended use | Current status |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `codex-01` | `codex` | ChatGPT/Codex seat for `dummy account` | Pending login |
| `codex-02` | `codex` | ChatGPT/Codex seat for `GeoWake App` | Pending login |
| `codex-03` | `codex` | ChatGPT/Codex seat for `Hazzy` | Pending login |
| `codex-04` | `codex` | ChatGPT/Codex seat for `Raed` | Pending login |
| `codex-05` | `codex` | ChatGPT/Codex seat for `raed siddiqui` | Pending login |
| `codex-06` | `codex` | ChatGPT/Codex seat for `stuff rand (You)` | Pending login |
| `google-main` | `google` | Google coding-plan account (`youaretalkingtoraed@gmail.com`) | Pending login |
| `copilot-raed2180416` | `github-copilot` | GitHub Copilot account `Raed2180416` | Pending login |
| `copilot-accneww432` | `github-copilot` | GitHub Copilot account `accneww432` | Pending login |

## Safe Login Order

1. `codex-06`
2. `google-main`
3. `copilot-raed2180416`
4. `copilot-accneww432`
5. remaining `codex-*` slots

Reason:

- validate the Codex slot that corresponds to the screenshot entry marked `(You)` first
- validate one non-OpenAI provider path second
- confirm GitHub Copilot auth works before scaling to all Codex seats

## Operator Rule

When `arctic-slot-login.sh` asks for the account label you actually authenticated, enter the canonical label from this table exactly.

## Post-Login Verification

After each slot login:

1. run `bash audit-map/16-scripts/arctic-slot-status.sh`
2. inspect the slot snapshot in `18-snapshots/accounts/<slot>/`
3. if authentication succeeded, optionally refresh visible models for that slot:
   - `bash audit-map/16-scripts/arctic-slot-models.sh --slot <slot> --refresh`

